The paper discusses the development of an artificial creative agent using deep generative autoencoder, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep neural nets for generating new digits suggests that the paper could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also touches upon the concept of knowledge-driven creativity, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SD).
